At 08:21 PM 10/23/2009, SQUID wrote...
>watched this on GM, ..'other domestics" and "Euros", but there is 
>always a
>sequence.  They are presumably 12 volt, and is it the 'Wire loom 
>length' that
>creates this, due to resistance factors in different cars ..or?

They're not precision timing devices, so they don't have the same cycle 
times.

FMVSS 108 turn signal requirements cite SAE Standard J590b, which 
allows cycle times from 60-120 cycles per minute (depends somewhat on 
the duty cycle and type of flasher), so manufacturers have lots of 
leeway.
